Third-party licenses
====================

This project redistributes third-party runtime components in the Windows CLI package,
the desktop portable package, and the compiled desktop executable. Dependency versions
are fixed by package-lock.json and desktop-sample/src-tauri/Cargo.lock.

Claude Desktop translation memory
---------------------------------
Source: https://github.com/GMYXDS/claude-desktop-zh-simple
Embedded snapshot: 20260711180535, 19276 English-to-Simplified-Chinese mappings
License: Apache License 2.0
Source notice: desktop-sample/resources/claude/SOURCE.md
Full license: desktop-sample/resources/claude/APACHE-2.0.txt

The translation memory is embedded in the desktop executable and is used only to map
JSON string values in three Claude Desktop en-US.json resource files. The project does
not redistribute Claude Desktop, Claude.exe, app.asar, Anthropic assets, or account data.

Desktop runtime direct dependencies
-----------------------------------
Tauri 2: https://github.com/tauri-apps/tauri (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
ureq 3.3.0: https://github.com/algesten/ureq (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
rusqlite 0.40.1: https://github.com/rusqlite/rusqlite (MIT)
Serde and serde_json: https://github.com/serde-rs/serde (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
sha2 0.10: https://github.com/RustCrypto/hashes (MIT OR Apache-2.0)
base64 0.22: https://github.com/marshallpierce/rust-base64 (MIT OR Apache-2.0)

The complete resolved Rust dependency graph and exact versions are recorded in
desktop-sample/src-tauri/Cargo.lock. The Windows WebView2 runtime is supplied by the
operating system and is not redistributed by this project.

